<BODY background="" TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
Ron Oldfield and David Kotz.
<b>Scientific Applications using Parallel I/O</b>.
In
Hai Jin, Toni Cortes, and Rajkumar Buyya.
editors, 
<i>High Performance Mass Storage and Parallel I/O: Technologies
and Applications</i>,
chapter 45,
IEEE Computer Society Press and John Wiley &amp; Sons,
2001.
<p><b>Abstract:</b> Scientific applications are increasingly being implemented on
massively parallel supercomputers. Many of these applications have intense
I/O demands, as well as massive computational requirements. This paper is
essentially an annotated bibliography of papers and other sources of
information about scientific applications using parallel I/O.</p>
<p><b>Keywords:</b> parallel-IO, parallel computing, file system</p>
